If the number of troops on a system falls below the established garrison requirement, or if the Empire conducts a successful mission to incite an uprising, the population of that system will revolt.  A system in such a state is said to be in 'uprising', and all production on that system ceases.   If the uprising is not shortly subdued, facilities on that system may eventually be destroyed, or the planet may even desert the Alliance and join the Empire!  Uprisings can be subdued by placing twice the normal garrison on the system or by sending a character to perform a 'Subdue Uprising' mission at that location. While these measures can be taken to subdue such a situation, I strongly suggest not allowing our systems to go into uprising.